DOCUMENT 8 — WEEKLY FOUNDER DASHBOARD (POP)

Rejoin Media | Knowledge Library

Purpose
To maintain focus on the single biggest constraint, drive weekly progress, and create a tight feedback loop between action and learning.

This dashboard applies the Physics of Progress (POP) framework on a weekly cadence.

WEEKLY DASHBOARD STRUCTURE

This dashboard should be completed once per week and reviewed briefly mid-week if needed.

1. Weekly Objective (One Only)

This week, the single outcome that matters is:

Rules

Must be specific and measurable

Must plausibly move revenue, clarity, or confidence

If achieved, the week is a win regardless of everything else

2. Bottleneck Hypothesis

The current bottleneck is:

Why this is the bottleneck (1 sentence):

Rule:
If you can’t name the bottleneck, you’re not allowed to add tasks.

3. Hypothesis for Progress (POP Step)

If I do ______________________, then ______________________ will improve because ______________________.

Keep it simple. One lever.

4. Actions to Test the Hypothesis (Max 3)

List 1–3 concrete actions only.

Rules

Actions must be uncomfortable enough to matter

No “prep” tasks unless they directly enable action

Fewer actions = higher odds of completion

5. Non-Goals (Explicit Exclusions)

This week, I am not allowed to work on:

Purpose:
Protects focus and prevents disguised avoidance.

6. Mid-Week Check (Optional, 2 Minutes)

Answer quickly:

Did I take at least one action that directly addresses the bottleneck? (Yes / No)

If no, what did I avoid?

No fixing. Just awareness.

7. Friday Review (POP Feedback Loop)

Complete during your Friday Proof Sweep.

A. What Actually Happened

Actions taken:

Observable results:

Unexpected outcomes:

B. What Worked
C. What Didn’t
D. Why (Pattern, Not Excuse)
8. Learning Captured

One sentence insight to carry forward:

(If this is proof-related, it goes into Proof Inbox — Raw.)

9. Next Week’s Leading Indicator

If next week is going well, I will see this by Wednesday:

This becomes next week’s early warning signal.

OPERATING RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

One dashboard per week — no retrospectives months later

If the week feels “busy” but unclear, the dashboard was skipped

Bottleneck > actions > learning > adjustment

Progress is directional, not perfect

